.TH "merge_va_blocks_locked" 9 "merge_va_blocks_locked" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
merge_va_blocks_locked \- merge a virtual block if possible.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" merge_va_blocks_locked
.BI "(struct hl_device *hdev "  ","
.BI "struct list_head *va_list "  ","
.BI "struct hl_vm_va_block *va_block "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "hdev" 12
pointer to the habanalabs device structure.
.IP "va_list" 12
pointer to the virtual addresses block list.
.IP "va_block" 12
virtual block to merge with adjacent blocks.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This function does the following:
- Merge the given blocks with the adjacent blocks if their virtual ranges
create a contiguous virtual range.

This Function should be called only when va_list lock is taken.
